    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-26T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">674.84A/8–2652: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 474<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d474fn1">Repeated to London and Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-26T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 26, 1952—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> told me (re <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 368, Aug 20) this eve that his program is
                    in fol order: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>To put the internal sit straight.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>To negotiate for Middle East def.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>To reach agrmt with Israel.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>At this point I must remind Dept with emphasis that during the first winter after
                    my arrival here under <persName corresp="#p_AMG1">Sirry</persName> Govt I was
                    able to persuade <persName corresp="#p_AMG1">Sirry</persName> and the Palace to
                    promise to try reach agrmt with <pb facs="1028" n="988" xml:id="pg_988"/> Israel
                    and that on two occasions leaks came out to Tel Aviv and the Egypts dropped the
                    whole business like a very hot brick.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
